sql:
SELECT zone_name, location, contact_email
FROM zones
WHERE zone_id = 0;

SELECT *
FROM readme_files
WHERE upload_date > '2022-12-31';

SELECT ms.station_name, z.contact_email
FROM monitoring_stations ms
JOIN zones z ON ms.zone_id = z.zone_id;

SELECT zone_code, zone_name 
FROM zones
WHERE zone_id > 5;

external_knowledge:
- 'identity numbers of the devices' refers to `sensor_id`;
- 'names of the devices' refers to `sensor_name`;
- 'current conditions' refers to `status`;
- 'situated in the area known as 'ZoneA'' refers to the zone named 'ZoneA'.

sql:
SELECT collection_date, max_value
FROM data_statistics
WHERE station_id = 1 AND count > 0;

SELECT count, HEX(mean), median
FROM data_statistics
WHERE stat_id = 1 AND station_id = 1;

external_knowledge:
- "hidden treasures" refers to the sought-after data; 
- "veins of raw data" symbolizes the flow and interconnected nature of the data collections;
- "network of sensors, stations, and zones" refers to the structure of the data collection system;
- "essence of the elements they sense" metaphorically refers to the values of the collected data;
- "journey of each data point’s origin" refers to the collection date, time of collection, sensor ID, and related sensor-type, station, and zone information;
- "quality" refers to the measurement of data quality;
- "source of its enlightenment" symbolizes the source of the data.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT user_id) AS user_count
FROM data_comments
WHERE data_id = 10;

SELECT value 
FROM data_collections 
WHERE value > 100;

external_knowledge:
- 'Maintenance status not completed' means the sensor has ongoing or pending maintenance issues;
- 'Nearing the end of their energy reserves' metaphorically refers to a battery level below 80%;
- 'Barely whispering their signals' is a figurative way to describe very low signal strength, specifically less than 2;
- 'Identities' refer to the sensor IDs;
- 'Last times they sought care' refer to the last maintenance dates;
- 'Classification' refers to the sensor type names.

- "Beacons" metaphorically represents the monitoring stations;
- "Realms" metaphorically represents the zones;
- "Dawn of the first day of the new year" refers to the date '2023-01-01';
- "Unveil their secrets" refers to revealing the collected data values;
- "In ascending order of significance" refers to ordering by the collected values in ascending order.

sql:
SELECT st.sensor_type_name, s.sensor_name, s.status
FROM sensors s
LEFT JOIN sensor_types st ON s.sensor_type_id = st.sensor_type_id;
